adjectives.description: outgoing (comparative more outgoing, superlative most outgoing)

entries.meaning: Extraverted: talkative, friendly, and social, especially with respect to meeting new people easily and comfortably.
examples: Tom is very outgoing and enjoys meeting people; his brother, on the other hand, is painfully shy.

entries.meaning: (not comparable) Going out, on its way out.
(not comparable) Being replaced in office (while still in office but after election has determined that he/she will be replaced).
examples: The outgoing politician wasn't too disappointed he'd lost the election; he was tired of political infighting.

entries.meaning: The act of leaving or going out; exit, departure.
examples: the outgoings of the morning and evening

entries.meaning: (chiefly in the plural) Money that leaves one's possession; expenditure, outlay, expense.
The extreme limit; the place of ending.
examples: The outgoings of the border were at the north bay of the salt sea, at the south end of Jordan.
